# Fibonacci — compute the Nth fibonacci number
#
# Stack trick: keep two values [b, a] on the stack.
# Each step: SWAP the pair, OVER copies the new top,
# ADD combines them. After N steps, the result is on top.
#
# 0 1 -> 1 0 -> 1 1 -> 1 1 -> 2 1 -> 2 2 -> 3 2 ...

# Start: a=0, b=1. Iterate 20 times. Drop the spare.
0 1 20 { SWAP OVER ADD } TIMES SWAP DROP SAY DROP

# Result: 10946
